<LP>
   TOKYO -- Nomura Securities Co. announced Friday that it
will establish a representative office in West Berlin to
collect information on the rapid changes expected in the
eventual unification of East and West Germany.
   Nomura becomes the second Japanese financial institution
to open an office in Berlin, a Nomura official said. The Bank
of Tokyo Ltd. started doing business in East Berlin June 1.
Nomura's new office will start operations Monday.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   With the new office, the number of Nomura's subsidiaries
and representative offices overseas comes to 54 in 23
countries.
